reviews.review_text:
this is the better version This is the better AUD of this show, this is the one to get. Still searching for the SBD of the second set, desperately searching!
This Speedway is my very favorite. Second set is great, first set is.....not.

Agree w/ spinner that this is the best of the 3 versions available now, but I don't think it's worth nearly 4 stars.  The audience is louder than the band, and that's just not right.  I don't mind hearing some audience for ambiance, but to hear them drown out the band at every exciting moment is un-enjoyable.  Please can we get a SBD of this show because the energy of the band is high and I'd love to experience it fully.

Where are the 95 sbds????? How are we in 2023 and there STILL aren't many sbds of these critical shows from the end of Jerry's performing career??  And there are many sbds from the last 2 tours that sound muddy and hissy.  I heard that they didn't hand out patches as much toward the last few years but there are tons of 94 sbds... is it because nobody cares about 95 shows???  I will say there are some boards that sound amazing from 95 spring tour but then you'll get to the next show and nada.  Maybe someone can post on here and explain or even better, do something about it for us true deadheads who don't just listen to spring 90 or cirnel 77 on repeat.
